This is an often heard claim, but if you start to examine it it falls
apart. We can definitely build the pyramids today if we wanted to -
the stones are well within what cranes can handle. The other
structures are much less complex - try comparing the size of (say)
Acropolis with a modern skyscraper or cathedral. Still, it is
impressive that they managed to build them.

