As you can see from my new .signature, I have now installed BeOS on my
machine.  I am also typing this message on a Dvorak keyboard.  In the
last election, I voted Libertarian where possible.  I'm a
Singularitarian, and thus by extension a transhumanist, a
science-fiction fan, and a novelty-seeker.  Coincidence?  I think not. 
For some people, There Is A Better Way.

Let us consider:  Is someone running MacOS or Linux or BeOS, even though
95% of the planet uses Windows, more likely to use the Dvorak keyboard,
even though 95% of the planet uses QWERTY?  Is someone who votes
Libertarian more likely to be a transhumanist?  I have no hard
statistics on the subject, but I suspect that there is considerable
overlap between the groups.

I'd like to list the following items for a Better Way Award.  The Better
Way Awards are given to Ways (1) that inspire fanatic devotion in their
users and (2) that only a minority use - and, of course, are vastly
Better than the alternatives.

   Vastly Better Way Awards:

BeOS:              There Is A Better Operating System.
Linux/OpenSource:  There Is A Better Development Strategy.
Dvorak:            There Is A Better Keyboard.
Libertarianism:    There Is A Better Political Party.
Design Patterns:   There Is A Better Design Method.
Science Fiction:   There Is A Better Literature.
Singularity/>H:    There Is A Better Goal.
Cryonics:          There Is A Better Survival Strategy.
Nanotechnology:    There Is A Better Material World.

   Better Way Awards (category 1):

XML:               There Is A Better Data Format.
PGP/RSA:           There Is A Better Cryptographic Cipher.
Godel Escher Bach: There Is A Better Book.
Software Reuse:    There Is A Better Development Strategy.
Object-Orientation:There Is A Better Programming Paradigm.

   Better Way Awards (category 2):

arXiv/cogprints:   There Is A Better Scientific Paper Repository.
OnSale's atCost:   There Is A Better (and Vastly Cheaper) Seller.
Evolution. Psych:  There Is A Better Psychology.
Credit Unions:     There Is A Better Bank.
IBM Solutions:     There Is A Better Software Search Engine.
Good Drug Guide:   There Is A Better Neurology.
Collaborative Filtering:    T.I.A.B. Way of Finding Things.
Rutan's Rotor:     There Is A Better Spaceship.
Australia:         There Is A Better Country.  (Planning to move someday...)
Ask Jeeves:        There Is A Better Search-Engine Interface.

   Slightly Better Way Awards:

USA:               There Is A Better Country.
Python:            There Is A Better Programming Language.
Java:              There Is A Better Programming Language.
Scheme:            There Is A Better Programming Language.
Eiffel:            There Is A Better Programming Language.
User Friendly:     There Is A Better Comic Strip.
Extropians:        There Was A Better Mailing List (pre-1998 only).

What are *your* Better Ways?
